title: Bug 109350: Output parameter should display in data set dialog.
OB: When calling the stored procedure from an Oracle database, the query result is stored in the output parameter as an object. However, in the query result page, no data is returned.
EB: The output parameter should be displayed in the edit data set dialog.
SR: To reproduce: 1. Call the stored procedure from an Oracle database. 2. Check the query result page and observe that the output parameter is not displayed in the edit data set dialog.
